definition.value: A vitamin B6 phosphate that is the  phosphoric ester derivative of pyridoxamine.
An androstanoid that is dehydroepiandrosterone carrying an additional hydroxy substituent at the 7beta-position. It is a metabolite of dehydroepiandrosterone.
An N-glycosyl compound that consists of 5,6-diaminouracil in which one of the hydrogens on the 6-amino function is substituted by a 5-phospho-beta-D-ribosyl residue.
An organic chloride salt of thiamine(1+) monophosphate.
